Project 2: Mobile Testing for Spotify App - Playlist Creation
Scenario: Unable to create a new playlist

Steps Reproduce:

1-) Open the Spotify app on a mobile device.
2-) Tap on the “Your Library” tab.
3-) Click on “Create Playlist.”
4-) Enter a name for the new playlist and tap “Create.”

Expected Result: A new playlist should be created, and the user should be able to add songs to it.

Actual Result: After tapping "Create," an error message appears: "Unable to create a playlist at this time. Please try again later."

Severity: Medium
Priority: High
Bug Type: Functional
Environment: iOS 16.1, iPhone 13
Attachments:

Screenshot: Playlist_Error.jpg
Video: Playlist_Error_Screen.mp4
